Generic single-database configuration.

# introduction

Database migrations

# Getting Started

1- To create a migration for the first time, execute the following command

$ alembic revision --autogenerate -m "migration name"

The same command can be used to generate a new migrations

2- Verify the alembic autogenerated db scripts

3- To apply migrations, execute the following command. This will to create/update tables in the database

$ alembic upgrade head
